<Window x:Class="Kompano.src.UI.About.About"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             xmlns:local="clr-namespace:Kompano.src.UI.About"
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             Title="About Kompano" Height="350" Width="520" Background="#f2f2f2"
            ResizeMode="NoResize"
            WindowStyle="SingleBorderWindow" WindowStartupLocation="CenterScreen"
            Icon="/Kompano;component/src/Addin/Resources/KompanoProfileIcon.ico">

    <Grid Margin="0">
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="155"/>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="*"/>
            

        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>


        <!-- Profile Section -->

        <Border Grid.Column="0">
            <Image Name="KompanoProfile" />

        </Border>


        <!-- Info Section -->

        <Border Grid.Column="1" Margin="5,0,5,0">
            <StackPanel>
                <TextBlock Text="Kompano Revit Tool" Margin="0,10,0,10" />

                <TextBlock Text="Version 1.0.4   © 2024 Formode" Margin="0,0,0,10" />

               

               
                <Border  BorderBrush="Black" BorderThickness="0.5" Height="200" >
                    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                        <TextBlock  TextWrapping="Wrap"  Margin="5,5,5,5" >
                            Kompano is an architect. Over time, he has realized that he has over 200 Revit families in his repositories and directories. 
                            He hardly uses some of them, not out of choice but by circumstance. Opening each and every Revit family to check how it looks is a 
                            tedious process that Kompano has no time for.
                            
                            <LineBreak />
                            <LineBreak />
                            Additionally, Kompano intends to create his BIM portfolio. He has a wide array of over 120 models completed over the years to select samples from. 
                            Kompano cannot fathom opening each one individually, 
                            let alone the tedious process of exporting images. He needs a quick solution.
                            <LineBreak />
                            <LineBreak />
                            
                            This tool, named after Kompano, simplifies the visualization process of Revit families and projects. 
                            It auto-opens upto 100 Revit families/projects, creates stunning and consistent isometric visuals, gathers the visuals into one folder 
                            ,and finally auto closes the files all within a timeframe of 5 minutes!
                            
                            <LineBreak />
                            <LineBreak />
                            Try it out today!
                            <LineBreak />
                            <LineBreak />
                            Designed by: Symon Kipkemei: symon@formode.ke 
                            <LineBreak />
                            https://www.formode.ke
                            <LineBreak />

                        </TextBlock>



                    </ScrollViewer>
                </Border>
                <Button Content="OK" Width="80" Height="25"  Click="OkButton_Click" Margin="0,10,0,0"
                        Background="#f57c00" Foreground="White" FontWeight="Bold" HorizontalAlignment="Right"/>

            </StackPanel>
        </Border>

    </Grid>
    
</Window>
